Vice President Kamala Harris met virtually with 15 leaders representing Caribbean nations to discuss partnerships and cooperation on economic recovery, climate crisis, and security. She proposed an annual meeting of this group to continue high-level discussions. The Vice President emphasized equitable economic growth in the Caribbean and ways to facilitate trade and attract U.S. investment. She also announced increased assistance through the Caribbean Basin Security Initiative for combating firearms trafficking, enhancing maritime security, and supporting training for police. The leaders also discussed cooperation on addressing the climate crisis and transitioning to clean energy. They agreed to stay in close touch, including at the upcoming Summit of the Americas in Los Angeles.